com.github.javaparser.ast.type

Class IntersectionType

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.javaparser.ast.Node
      • com.github.javaparser.ast.type.Type
        • com.github.javaparser.ast.type.IntersectionType
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    NodeWithAnnotations<IntersectionType>, NodeWithRange<Node>, NodeWithTokenRange<Node>, Observable, Visitable, HasParentNode<Node>, Resolvable<Object>, Cloneable

    public final class IntersectionType
extends Type
implements NodeWithAnnotations<IntersectionType>
    Represents a set of types. A given value of this type has to be assignable to at all of the element types. As of Java 8 it is used in casts or while expressing bounds for generic types.

    For example: public class A<T extends Serializable & Cloneable> { }

    Or: void foo((Serializable & Cloneable)myObject);

    Since:
    3.0.0
